HEADWORD: Counteraction
<hw>Coun`ter*ac"tion</hw> <pr>(koun`t?r-?k"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>Action in opposition; hindrance resistance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[They] do not . . . overcome the <qex>counteraction</qex> of a
false principle or of stubborn partiality.</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counteractive</ent>⟦br⟧
